[{"id":"UgyqOPJrmjSXG65eZep4AaABAg","parent":"root","text":"Reminds me of mk64 and double dash","like_count":0,"author_id":"UCRRJETfmyJ0qmLnFXCRkdiQ","author":"@ryfyyt171","author_thumbnail":"https://yt3.ggpht.com/wlE_g89PtVepsy7KKhpRm33FbqGXixDEabHrC50LredMftLF5VXt4soTZr1r-UtS3LgtfbH7wu4=s88-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj","author_is_uploader":false,"author_url":"https://www.youtube.com/@ryfyyt171","is_favorited":false,"timestamp":1619568000,"is_pinned":false},{"id":"UghZf3vg-dUVv3gCoAEC","parent":"root","text":"It's really good for something made in two days :3","like_count":0,"author_id":"UCirFwTUr0JjsnP-eq5vjm0w","author":"@NexDigilit","author_thumbnail":"https://yt3.ggpht.com/ytc/AIdro_lCogi-1D-Cs9oynKmy-SbuWmerMHZ7VenPF48O8BcC2PM=s88-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj","author_is_uploader":false,"author_url":"https://www.youtube.com/@NexDigilit","is_favorited":false,"timestamp":1430179200,"is_pinned":false},{"id":"UghZf3vg-dUVv3gCoAEC.7-H0Z7-R53g7-H6CvOaLOi","parent":"UghZf3vg-dUVv3gCoAEC","text":"I know, it's a pretty good achievement for someone lazy like me  =D\nBut I feel that I might've used a wrond kind of sample for the main melody here (top-right), 'cuz it sounded surprisingly off-pitch when it was played along with the original song in the collab.  =/\nWell, lesson learned, I'll just have to practice more, and probably use FLStudio for the audio instead of Sony Vegas pitch-shifting.  =)","like_count":0,"author_id":"UCwiGSPpRzQkw80OKDeN8Wvw","author":"@FinnOtaku","author_thumbnail":"https://yt3.ggpht.com/ytc/AIdro_nNsIn_qk_ULwmmn7XM9pL6v_Rm_z5xiQ_a8zw3TdU8gUA=s88-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj","author_is_uploader":true,"author_url":"https://www.youtube.com/@FinnOtaku","is_favorited":false,"timestamp":1430179200,"is_pinned":false},{"id":"UghZf3vg-dUVv3gCoAEC.7-H0Z7-R53g7-I6KrEtZvI","parent":"UghZf3vg-dUVv3gCoAEC.7-H0Z7-R53g7-H6CvOaLOi","text":"But its a bit difficult to do it in fl studio. also it doesn't sound very good. I'm switching over to Reaper.","like_count":0,"author_id":"UC